      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: recover MCP OAuth sessions after token refresh",
        "body": "Closes #98377.\n\n## What Problem This Solves\nLong-running gateway MCP sessions could stay stuck after OAuth access-token expiry when the refreshed bearer was rejected on the old streamable HTTP MCP session.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nThe session MCP runtime now treats OAuth streamable HTTP 401s as stale-session failures, retires the current MCP transport once, rebuilds the catalog/session, and replays the request through the existing refresh-token path. Static-header and non-OAuth MCP failures keep the existing failure/backoff behavior.\n\n## User Impact\nHeadless gateways can recover OAuth-protected remote MCP servers without requiring a manual `openclaw mcp login` while a valid refresh token exists.\n\n## Evidence\nAdded deterministic streamable HTTP OAuth regressions for catalog refresh, direct tool calls, and failed retry/backoff preservation.\n\nReal behavior proof with the actual session MCP runtime against a local streamable-http OAuth/MCP server:\n\n```text\nproof setup: initial long-lived MCP session established; token then expired server-side\nproof result: tool call recovered on a fresh MCP session without manual login\nproof counts: token_refreshes=1 initialize_calls=2\nredacted server transcript:\n- initialize session=- token=initial-access -> 200 stale-session\n- notifications/initialized session=stale-session token=initial-access -> 202\n- tools/list session=stale-session token=initial-access -> 200\n- tools/call session=stale-session token=initial-access -> 401 invalid_token\n- POST /token session=- token=refresh-token -> 200 refreshed-access\n- tools/call session=stale-session token=refreshed-access -> 401 stale_mcp_session\n- initialize session=- token=refreshed-access -> 200 fresh-session\n- notifications/initialized session=fresh-session token=refreshed-access -> 202\n- tools/list session=fresh-session token=refreshed-access -> 200\n- tools/call session=fresh-session token=refreshed-access -> 200 ok:fresh-session\n```\n",
        "branch": "fix-98377-mcp-oauth-gateway-refresh",
